Text.Value: This is meant to be flattery, not poetry. Just tell me I'm beautiful and we can call it a day.
Oh pardon, I didn't want to inconvenience you with my age-old curse.
Just looking. What are you doing?
You're pretty good. Not 'Gale' good, but pretty good.
Very good. Now just tell me I'm beautiful and we can call it a day.
Your mole definitely grabs my attention.
So is the tadpole causing all that sagging skin, or...
I see you.
Another quirk of my affliction.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion watches the player in the mirror as they move through the space where his reflection should be.
EditorData.NodeContext: Astarion watches the player in the mirror as they move through the space where his reflection should be.

Text.Value: An elven vampire spawn, approximately 5'11", medium build...
Do you miss it? Seeing your own face?
I'd better get some beauty sleep. It seems I need it if I'm to catch up with the competition.
When you smile, your face wrinkles. It is comforting.
Your mole is impressively large.
Mirrors aren't much use, but being reflected in someone else's eyes?
My - what? But I don't...
To you, maybe. To me it's just another thing Cazador took.
Stare into his eyes, taking in every detail of his face.
Is it? What do you see when you look at me?
I'm a vampire - forever young.
Looking at something?

EditorData.AnimationTags: [PaulN] Astarion is standing with back to player Idle, holding something (mirror) in his hands and looking into it, not obvious yet to player what it is.
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: With his back turned to you. He's holding a mirror, but you can't see it yet.
EditorData.NodeContext: With his back turned to you. He's holding a mirror, but you can't see it yet.

Text.Value: I've never even seen this face. Not since it grew fangs and my eyes turned red.
Your unsightly mole...
Suit yourself.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [PaulN] AST stares down at the mirror in his hands, watching you leave
EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He stares down at the mirror in his hands, watching you go
EditorData.NodeContext: He stares down at the mirror in his hands, watching you go

Text.Value: How dare you! I thought we had something special.
You're beautiful.
Sure, but was your mole always so... prominent?
Observant.
I see someone wasting my time.
The creases when you laugh.
It's an indulgence, I'll grant you, but a weakness? A well-presented face can open a lot of doors.
Oh. Go on...
Is that all you want? Shallow praise?
You can do better. What else?
But failing any of those, I will always settle for shallow praise.
Karlach is beautiful. You're fine, though.
That dangerous smile.
It's for the best, you're not exactly ageing gracefully.
What are you talking about? My skin isn't... is it?
Have a good night.
My face is just some dark shape in my past. Another thing I've lost.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: He hurls the mirror to the ground.
EditorData.NodeContext: He hurls the mirror to the ground.

Text.Value: Excuse me? I'm an eternally young vampire, not your doting grandmother.
Honestly, Wyll's more my type.
Funny. And what do you see, exactly?
Really? Anything in particular?
You don't have Lae'zel's charm, but you're all right.
I'm looking too, but not seeing very much.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Holds up a mirror to show how he could see you
EditorData.NodeContext: Holds up a mirror to show how he could see you

Text.Value: Despite being neither brave nor intelligent, you are one of the finest killers I've ever seen.
It's a small price to pay for a vampire's power.
No, I was just leaving.
The only benefit to a mirror when you have my condition.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Holds up a mirror to show how he could see you
EditorData.NodeContext: Holds up a mirror to show how he could see you

Text.Value: What?
...Excuse me.
Hardly. There's also gold, sex, revenge - quite the list, really.
Ageing? What do you mean 'ageing'?
Let's leave it there, shall we? It's been a long day and I've had all the compliments I can take.
The way your hair curls around your ears.
What colour were they before?
I'll be your mirror. What do you want to know?
Not that I've seen this face. Not since it grew fangs and its eyes turned red.
You're fine. Now Shadowheart - there's a beauty!
Count yourself lucky. I have to see this mug every day.
Strong, piercing eyes.
I'm kidding, you look great.
I... I don't know. I can't remember.
Your eyes are pleasing.
Gods above. Would it kill you to dispense a compliment?
It doesn't quite make up for the lack of a reflection, mind you.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Astarion watches the player in the mirror as they move through the space where his reflection should be.
EditorData.NodeContext: Astarion watches the player in the mirror as they move through the space where his reflection should be.

Text.Value: You have nothing to worry about - it's a very good face.
...Right. I, um...

EditorData.NodeContext: He just 'complimented' you by calling you stupid and a coward, but a good killer.

Text.Value: I want to know what the world sees when it looks at me. What you see.
For you maybe, but I like what I see.
Vanity is a weakness.
Still. You're nice too.
And what do you see, exactly?
Well, I could do worse.
How did you know I was here?
Preening in the looking glass? Petty vanity? Of course I miss it.

Synopsis: You find him sitting by the river (or with a mirror), staring at his non-reflection. He doesn't even remember what he looks like any more, it's been so long since he's seen his own face. You can lovingly describe his face to him or gaslight him, talking about unsightly moles that he doesn't actually have.
